      "summary": "The decisions page uses a single `acting` boolean to disable ALL decision cards during any single approve/deny operation, blocking unrelated decisions",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "design_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "app/decisions/page.tsx"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "app/decisions/page.tsx line 287: `const [acting, setActing] = useState(false)`",
          "Lines 346-358 and 361-374: handleApprove and handleDeny both set acting=true globally before their await, then acting=false in finally",
          "Lines 516-520: all DecisionCard instances receive the same acting prop \u2014 approving decision A disables decision B's buttons even though they are independent operations"
        ],
        "suggestion": "Replace the global acting flag with per-decision acting state: `const [actingIds, setActingIds] = useState<Set<string>>(new Set())`. In handleApprove/handleDeny, add/remove the specific decision id. Pass `acting={actingIds.has(decision.id)}` to each DecisionCard. This allows concurrent independent decisions.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
